      "writtenOn": "2026-07-01T13:57:51Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Patch set 2 addresses the review comments and hardens the opt-in path.\n\nThe per-NUMA setting now clearly represents Ginkgo workers rather than\nCPUs. Wide MW suites use one worker per NUMA node, while narrow suites\nuse an automatically selected worker count based on the smallest node.\n\nCPU allocation now handles Linux CPU lists directly, respects reserved\ncores, keeps allocations NUMA-local, and rejects overlaps. Parser unit\ntests were added.\n\nMASQUE MW tests are now registered through explicit TCP, UDP,\nHTTP/3 TCP, and control helpers. Each group becomes an independent\nOrdered suite when MW parallelism is enabled. A separate narrow helper\nis available for lightweight tests, while disabled mode still creates\none Serial Ordered suite containing all MASQUE MW tests.\n\nSplit repeats now rerun the complete phase sequence. Phase reports are\nmerged and aggregate counts and elapsed time are printed. Labels,\ngrouping, worker selection, and repeat behavior are documented.\n\nThe HST CI action enables MW parallelism for release and debug jobs\nusing TEST_JOBS\u003dauto. Fixed-count jobs retain serial MW execution.",
      "revId": "f99ea5215c2a0d79d602fe0cd3b03c118ce0128b",
      "serverId": "6d2eb258-4fe2-443e-8a38-ca81da23d4c2"
    },
